oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Taylor & Wrye Studio portrait photograph of a woman, Nashville, Tennessee, circa 1890s
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A studio portrait of an unknown woman, in the style of a 19th century cabinet card. The photographer was Taylor & Wrye, Broad and Vine Streets, Nashville, Tennessee as stamped on the card. Forms part of the Helon Daniel Miller Collection. 1 cabinet card.
